<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-116-104 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 019 090</DOCID><JOURNAL>IBM System User  July 1991 v12 n7 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Toshiba T2000SX. (Personal Computer Reviews) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wheelwright, Geoff.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Toshiba Corp's T2000SX notebook computer has modestspecifications.andP;  It contains a 16MHz processor, rather than the20MHz version of Intel's 386SX processor and has a 20Mbyte harddrive, instead of the 40Mbyte and 60Mbyte drives offered bycompeting machines.andP;  The T2000SX has 1Mbyte of RAM and a highlyreadable backlit VGA display.andP;  The power management software isexcellent and the battery life is the best of any 386SX system.andO;Optional internal modems and docking stations are available.andP;  Thebase price of 3,395 pounds sterling is high for a notebook.andP;  IfToshiba improved the machine with a 20MHz processor, or better,and a 40Mbyte to 80Mbyte hard drive this would be a verycompetitive machine.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Toshiba Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    TOSHB.andO;Product:   Toshiba T2000SX (Portable computer) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Notebook ComputersProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>